Thank you @WillLillis ! I can confirm it works. For everyone else, here is a lazy.nvim plugin file for the updated haskell parser:

```
return {
  'romus204/tree-sitter-manager.nvim',
  config = function()
    require('tree-sitter-manager').setup({
      ensure_installed = {
        'haskell',
      },
      auto_install = true,
      languages = {
        haskell = {
          install_info = {
            revision = "98aedbd2d6947a168ba3ba3755d70b0cb6b78395",
            url = "https://github.com/tree-sitter-grammars/tree-sitter-haskell",
          },
        },
      },
    })
  end,
}
```

This issue can be closed against neovim; here's a PR against TSM: 
https://github.com/romus204/tree-sitter-manager.nvim/pull/124
